2026-04-16 12:13:30 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Output Cable (+)', 'Control Switch terminal / joint where Control Output Cable (+) should connect'] hypothesis_explanation='The test result states that the Control Output Cable (+) has one disconnected (floating) end that was originally connected to the control switch. This means that when the switch is operated, the 12 V from the PSU/control input never reaches the load module; the series path to the lamp is open. Meanwhile, the control module red LED is powered because the module’s internal 12 V and 0 V rails are intact, and due to the wiring/indicator scheme it can still illuminate, giving the observed symptom set: power LED on, red LED on, but main lamp off. The root cause is therefore an open connection (broken or not properly terminated conductor or lug) on the Control Output Cable (+) at the switch/output interface. Repairing or replacing that cable/terminal to restore a solid connection from the switch output to the control module’s output connector should restore lamp operation.'
