DESCRIPTION: With power applied, disconnect the load module from the control module. Using a multimeter, identify which of the two output terminals of the control cube is at +12 V when the switch is ON (relative to its 0 V output). Then, on the load module, determine which input lead goes to the series diode and then to the lamps (this must be the +12 V input) and which goes to the return node. Verify whether, in the current connection, the control +12 V output is actually wired to the load’s +12 V/diode input and the 0 V output to the load’s return. Record if these are reversed or if either conductor is open.,
RESULT: Control Output Cable (−) is at +11.98 V relative to Control Output Cable (+), so the control cube’s (+) and (−) labeled outputs are reversed in terms of actual polarity. The load’s +12 V input (through the series diode to the lamps) is wired to Control Output Cable (+), and the load’s return is wired to Control Output Cable (−) with low resistance paths.
